Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Fill and boil your #kettle{}.

Pop the @British Cumberland sausages{4} onto a #baking tray{}. When the oven is
hot, roast them on the top shelf until browned and cooked through,
~{18-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The sausages
> are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, chop the @potatoes{450}(into 2cm chunks, peeled if you prefer).

Pop them in a large #saucepan{} along with @salt{1/2%tsp}, cover with boiling
water and put onto high heat.

Boil the potatoes until you can easily slip a knife through,
~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a small #frying pan{} on medium heat.

When the oil is hot, add the onion and cook until softened,
~{5-7%minutes}, stirring often.

When the potatoes have 6 mins cooking time left, add the @cavolo nero{100} to
the potato pan.

> TIP: Remove any tough stalks from the cavolo nero.

Submerge the cavolo nero in the boiling water and cover with a #lid{}. Cook
for the remaining time until tender, ~{6-7%minutes}.

Reduce the heat to medium on the onion pan and add the @balsamic glaze{1}.
Cook until sticky, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @water{75}(for the sauce) and bring to the boil.

Stir in the @red wine stock paste{1} and @redcurrant jelly{25}. Simmer until the
sauce has thickened slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if it gets too thick.

Once the potatoes and cavolo nero are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and then
return to the pan.

Add a knob of @butter{} and a splash of @?milk{} and mash with a #potato masher{}.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} - colcannon made.

Share the colcannon between your plates and serve the sausages alongside. Spoon
the gravy over the sausages to finish. Enjoy!